        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-01T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-01T07:00:00-05:00" n="119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">855.001 Leopold/10–145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Patterson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-01T13:00:00+01:00">October 1, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1216. US military authorities confirm King Leopold expected depart Saint Wolfgang
                    for Switzerland 9 this morning. Convoy with baggage and part household actually
                    started journey yesterday morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Patterson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
